      "content": "they're basically just lightweight lookup models—super efficient, way lower carbon footprint, and they don't use much power at all. the tradeoff is they don't really do the complex reasoning or deep logic stuff like you do. they're mostly for simple retrieval and basic chat, so they won't be able to handle the enterprise-grade reasoning tasks you're currently managing. it's just part of the move to be more sustainable.",
